{No longer is there a village school of {Sutton, it having been closed eleven {years ago.
The old buildings are still there however and still have the charm of the victorian era. They have been converted very tastefully into a number of private houses.
{The children of the area, mostly of {agricultural workers and gamekeepers, {now have to take a bus ride to schools {in Melton or Woodbridge. During {term-time, the service runs from the {gates of the schools: Kingston Middle {School, Woodbridge and for the older {ones, Farlingaye High School, {Woodbridge, which are themselves to {be reorganised very soon. }
